AN ACT relating to property insurance; creating the Fair Access to Insurance
Requirements Plan Association; requiring the membership of certain
authorized insurers in the Association; creating the Board of Directors
of the Association and prescribing the duties of the Board; requiring
the Board to establish the Fair Access to Insurance Requirements
(FAIR) Plan; establishing the requirements of the FAIR Plan; and
providing other matters properly relating thereto.
Legislative Counsel’s Digest:
1 Sections 2-18 of this bill provide for the establishment of the Fair Access to Insurance
2 Requirements (FAIR) Plan to provide property insurance coverage and commercial property
3 insurance coverage which results from the perils of fire or certain other perils when such
4 coverage is not otherwise available from an authorized insurer in this State. Sections 2-8
5 define certain terms relating to the FAIR Plan. Section 9 creates the Fair Access to Insurance
6 Requirements Plan Association to establish, offer and maintain the FAIR Plan. Section 9
7 requires any authorized insurer that offers or sells certain property insurance or commercial
8 property insurance in this State to be a member of the Association. Sections 10-12 create the
9 Board of Directors for the Association and prescribe the duties of the Board, which include
10 establishing the FAIR Plan, developing a plan of operation for the FAIR Plan and making
11 amendments to the plan of operation, subject to approval of the Commissioner of Insurance.
12 Section 12 establishes the required contents of the plan of operation for the FAIR Plan.
13 Sections 12 and 17 authorize the Commissioner to adopt regulations relating to the FAIR
14 Plan. Section 13 authorizes the Commissioner to revoke approval of all or part of the plan of
15 operation and make changes to the plan of operation if the plan of operation is insufficient.
16 Sections 14 and 15 establish provisions governing the issuance of policies and collecting
17 certain fees from Association members. Section 16 authorizes the Commissioner to take
18 certain actions against an Association member who fails to pay certain fees or otherwise
19 comply with the plan of operation for the FAIR Plan. Section 18 makes a final action or order
20 of the Commissioner relating to the FAIR Plan subject to judicial review.

