24 Sec. 9. 1. There is hereby created the Fair Access to Insurance
25 Requirements Plan Association, which is a nonprofit unincorporated public
26 entity. All Association members are and remain members of the Association as a
27 condition of the authority of each Association member to transact insurance or
28 reinsurance in this State.
29 2. The Association shall:
30 (a) Exercise its powers through the Board; and
31 (b) Perform its functions under a plan of operation established and approved
32 pursuant to section 12 of this act.
33 3. The Association is established to provide property insurance coverage
34 and commercial property insurance coverage when such coverage is not
35 otherwise available from an authorized insurer. The Association:
36 (a) Shall establish, offer and maintain a policy of property insurance and a
37 policy of commercial property insurance in accordance with the requirements of
38 the FAIR Plan.
39 (b) Shall assess and share among Association members, on a fair and
40 equitable basis, all expenses, income and losses based on the written premium of
41 each Association member for property insurance and commercial property
42 insurance consistent with sections 2 to 18, inclusive, of this act.
43 (c) May issue policies of property insurance and commercial property
44 insurance, reinsure any such policies in whole or in part, cede any such
45 reinsurance or transfer risk to other capital markets.
46 (d) Shall establish an Internet website available to the public which includes
47 information about the FAIR Plan. The Internet website must include a toll-free
48 telephone number that a person may use to obtain information about the FAIR
49 Plan.

